ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan reported 73 new COVID-19 cases during the last 24 hours, the country's ministry of health said on Saturday. The tally of infected people increased to 1,531,112 after adding the new cases, according to the data released by the ministry. A total of 30,381 people died from COVID-19 in Pakistan, with no more deaths recorded on Friday, according to the ministry's statistics. On Friday, 13,635 tests for COVID-19 were conducted in Pakistan while the positivity rate stood at 0.54 percent. Currently, there are 51 active cases in critical condition in the South Asian country.  â– 